# Zeno Classic Launcher — Windsurf AI Rules

## MANDATORY RULES — Follow for every code change

### No Worktrees
Never use git worktrees. Always work directly in the main repo directory.

### Full Workflow After Every Code Change

Step 1 — Full release build (always assembleRelease, never partial):
```
export JAVA_HOME="/Applications/Android Studio.app/Contents/jbr/Contents/Home"
./gradlew assembleRelease --no-daemon
```

Step 2 — Install on device:
```
adb install -r "app/build/outputs/apk/release/Zeno Classic.apk"
```
Shortcut: `./scripts/build-install.sh` does both steps.

Step 3 — Ask user to test:
Say "App installed. Please test it — does everything work correctly?"
Wait for response before doing anything else.

Step 4 — Commit only after user confirms:
```
git add <specific files changed>
git commit -m "description"
```
If it doesn't work: fix and restart from Step 1.

Step 5 — After commit, check push count:
```
git rev-list --count @{u}..HEAD
```
- Under 5: stay local
- 5 or more: remind user to push to origin/main

### Never
- Never partial builds (compileReleaseKotlin, assembleDebug) for device testing
- Never commit before user confirms device test passed
- Never git add . or git add -A
- Never force-push main
